Tested On: PI.
Classes Modified: Objectmanager.java , Actionhandler.java, and maybe Commands.java., client.java

adding the altar.

First go to objectmanager.java and search for 
[CODE]public void loadCustomSpawns(Client c) {[/CODE]

and add this under it ;
[CODE]c.getPA().checkObjectSpawn(409, XXXX, YYYY0, 10);[/CODE]

This is will spawn the Altar, at the XXXX and YYYY put the X coords and the Y coords, that will say at which place the altar will be , you can check this by doing ::mypost or ::coords, if you don't have ::mypos or ::coords add this to Commands.Java 

[CODE]if (playerCommand.equalsIgnoreCase("mypos")) {
			c.sendMessage("X: "+c.absX);
			c.sendMessage("Y: "+c.absY);
		}[/CODE]

Second, making it Restore prayer AND Special

First go to Actionhandler.java , and if you already have a altar added search for case 409, you will see somthing like this under it  ;

[CODE]if(c.playerLevel[5] < c.getPA().getLevelForXP(c.playerXP[5])) {
				c.startAnimation(645);
				c.playerLevel[5] = c.getPA().getLevelForXP(c.playerXP[5]);
				c.sendMessage("You recharge your prayer points.");
				c.getPA().refreshSkill(5);
			} else {
				c.sendMessage("You already have full prayer points.");
			}[/CODE]
under the last ' } ' add This ;[CODE]if(c.specAmount < 10.0){
				if (c.specRestore > 0) return;
				c.specRestore = 120;
				c.specAmount = 10.0;
				c.getItems().addSpecialBar(c.playerEquipment[c.playerWeapon]);
				c.sendMessage("Your special attack has been restored, only every 120 seconds.");
			}
			break;[/CODE]
if you don't have a altar added search for Break; and under it Add ;

[CODE]case 409:
if(c.playerLevel[5] < c.getPA().getLevelForXP(c.playerXP[5])) {
				c.startAnimation(645);
				c.playerLevel[5] = c.getPA().getLevelForXP(c.playerXP[5]);
				c.sendMessage("You recharge your prayer points.");
				c.getPA().refreshSkill(5);
			} else {
				c.sendMessage("You already have full prayer points.");
			}
			if(c.specAmount < 10.0){
				if (c.specRestore > 0) return;
				c.specRestore = 120;
				c.specAmount = 10.0;
				c.getItems().addSpecialBar(c.playerEquipment[c.playerWeapon]);
				c.sendMessage("Your special attack has been restored, only every 120 seconds.");
			}
			break;[/CODE]
if you don't want it to be 120 seconds just change [CODE]c.specRestore = 120;
[/CODE]  tho somthing else like 240= 3 mins

last but not least go to client.java and search for public int and add this somewhere with all the other ints

[CODE]public int specRestore = 0;[/CODE]

Then search for somthing like

[CODE]if(isDead && respawnTimer == -6) {
			getPA().applyDead();
		}[/CODE]

under that last } add

[CODE]if(specRestore > 0) {
			specRestore --;
		}[/CODE]

save compile and run :) that should do the trick, tought this was helpfull so posted this, if it's bad i will remove :)
